<div ana="#b1" corresp="#jeru0144.transcription" type="translation" xml:id="jeru0144.translation">
<p>Kyria</p>
</div>
</body>
<back>
<div type="commentary">
<p>Ossuary has inner ledge on three sides and a fragmentary flat, sliding lid. Name is inscribed on the chest's right side. The size of the ossuary indicates that it was intended for the remains of a child or adolescent, which supports the interpretation of קריה not as the word meaning "lady," but as a name derived from it. It is attested in Greek, as Κυρία, in Egypt, and at Bet She'arim in Jewish script. It appears on another ossuary from the same tomb group.</p>
</div>
